              "text": "{\n  \"voice\": \"Bold, utilitarian, and highly energetic. Stark black-and-white structural elements combined with punchy neon chartreuse accents evoke a modern, digital-native tool designed for quick creation. The UI typography remains strictly neutral and minimal, deliberately stepping back to let the chaotic, highly saturated user-generated meme content take center stage.\",\n  \"intent_conventions\": [\n    \"Active states and primary selections (like chosen tools, active slider tracks, or selected list items) consistently use a high-contrast neon chartreuse fill with black text or icons.\",\n    \"Floating toolbars and contextual menus utilize stark white, heavily rounded pill shapes with soft drop shadows to maintain visual separation from the canvas.\",\n    \"Dismissive or secondary actions (like 'Cancel') use solid black pill-shaped buttons with white text, contrasting sharply with the bright primary action buttons.\",\n    \"Canvas object selection is denoted by a thin, bright blue bounding box with square corner handles, ensuring high visibility against varied user imagery.\"\n  ],\n  \"exclusions\": [\n    \"No dark mode variants are observed; the system relies entirely on stark white surfaces for its panels and toolbars.\",\n    \"No serif or decorative typography is used in the UI, strictly adhering to a neutral sans-serif to avoid clashing with user content.\",\n    \"No sharp, 90-degree corners on UI components; everything from buttons to floating panels uses generous, pill-like border radii.\"\n  ],\n  \"style_lineage\": [\n    \"Reminiscent of modern mobile creative tools like Instagram Stories or Canva (floating pill menus, bottom sheets, soft shadows) crossed with the high-contrast, neon-and-black utilitarian aesthetic often seen in Web3 and digital-native youth brands.\"\n  ]\n}",
